    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-25T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-25T04:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114A/271</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-25T10:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 27, 2.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. [From <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName>]:</p>
                <p>The American delegation in order to expedite the work of the conference and
                    without binding upon future action believes it advisable to make in one of the
                    plenary meetings of the Prisoners of War Conference the following declaration:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The German delegation takes note of the statement by the American
                            delegation that while the Government of the United States makes no
                            commitment binding upon its future conduct, it is not its present <pb
                                facs="0185" n="101" xml:id="pg_101"/> practice or intention to
                            transport to the United States any of the prisoners captured by its land
                            forces who would be subject under the terms of this agreement to
                            compulsory labor.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>We very urgently ask whether you have any objection to such a declaration being
                    made. <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
